image.latex-image:
 \begin{tikzpicture}[thick,scale=1.75] [domain=-1:2]
   \draw [linecolor, line width=2pt] (0,0) -- (1,1) node [below] at (0,-0.2) {Home};
   \draw [linecolor, line width=2pt] (1,1) -- (0,2) node [above] at (0,2.2) {Second};
      \draw [linecolor, line width=2pt] (0,2) -- (-1,1) -- (0,0) node [right] at (1,1.2) {First}; 
      \draw [linecolor] node [left] at (-1.15,1) {Third};
   \fill [black] (-1,1) circle (3pt);
      \fill [black] (0,0) circle (4pt);
      \fill [black] (1,1) circle (3pt);
         \fill [black] (0,2) circle (3pt);
\end{tikzpicture}

solution.p:
By the Pythagorean Theorem, we know that x^2 + 90^2 = z^2;
differentiating with respect to t, we have

  2x\frac{dx}{dt} = 2z\frac{dz}{dt}
.
